cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CR 

The paper presents a novel algorithm for anomaly detection on large datasets and data streams, which involves kernel-based similarity estimation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given that the focus is on developing an efficient and scalable algorithm for anomaly detection, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
